# AVIATONLY Data Model and Workflow Rules

Avoid one giant AircraftListing table with many nullable fields.

Use a clean domain model.

Recommended core entities:

- User
- AircraftListing
- AircraftAirframe
- AircraftEngine
- AircraftPropeller
- AircraftAvionics
- AircraftMaintenance
- AircraftPhoto
- AircraftDocument
- ListingReviewTask
- ListingStatusHistory
- ListingEvent
- Lead
- Offer
- Deal
- Inspection
- Valuation
- Auction

## Listing Status

Use explicit statuses.

Recommended listing statuses:

- DRAFT
- SUBMITTED
- UNDER_REVIEW
- NEEDS_CHANGES
- VALUATION_READY
- INSPECTION_PENDING
- APPROVED_FOR_LISTING
- LIVE_FIXED_PRICE
- LIVE_AUCTION
- UNDER_OFFER
- DEPOSIT_PENDING
- UNDER_CONTRACT
- TRANSFER_PENDING
- SOLD
- WITHDRAWN

Do not allow arbitrary client-side status changes.

Only authorised server-side workflows should move listings into important statuses such as:

- APPROVED_FOR_LISTING
- LIVE_FIXED_PRICE
- LIVE_AUCTION
- UNDER_CONTRACT
- TRANSFER_PENDING
- SOLD

## Listing Status History

Every status change should be tracked.

Fields:

- id
- listingId
- fromStatus
- toStatus
- changedById
- reason
- createdAt

## Listing Event

Keep a generic event log for the activity timeline.

Fields:

- id
- listingId
- actorId
- type
- message
